comments.name: remarks
comments.value: Runs a command synchronously using the context of the broader dimenion.

comments.name: param
comments.value: Command to run. Note that command strings should not start with slash.

comments.name: returns
comments.value: Returns a command result with a count of successful values from the command.

comments.name: throws
comments.value:
Throws an exception if the command fails due to incorrect parameters or command syntax, or in erroneous cases for the command.
Note that in many cases, if the command does not operate (e.g., a target selector found no matches), this method will not throw an exception.
